(string) (len=2955) "COMMENT\t> \\brief \\b XERBLA\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*  =========== DOCUMENTATION ===========\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t* Online html documentation available at\nCOMMENT\t*            http://www.netlib.org/lapack/explore-html/\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*  Definition:\nCOMMENT\t*  ===========\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*       SUBROUTINE XERBLA( SRNAME, INFO )\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*       .. Scalar Arguments ..\nCOMMENT\t*       CHARACTER*(*)      SRNAME\nCOMMENT\t*       INTEGER            INFO\nCOMMENT\t*       ..\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*> \\par Purpose:\nCOMMENT\t*  =============\nCOMMENT\t*>\nCOMMENT\t*> \\verbatim\nCOMMENT\t*>\nCOMMENT\t*> XERBLA  is an error handler for the LAPACK routines.\nCOMMENT\t*> It is called by an LAPACK routine if an input parameter has an\nCOMMENT\t*> invalid value.  A message is printed and execution stops.\nCOMMENT\t*>\nCOMMENT\t*> Installers may consider modifying the STOP statement in order to\nCOMMENT\t*> call system-specific exception-handling facilities.\nCOMMENT\t*> \\endverbatim\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*  Arguments:\nCOMMENT\t*  ==========\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*> \\param[in] SRNAME\nCOMMENT\t*> \\verbatim\nCOMMENT\t*>          SRNAME is CHARACTER*(*)\nCOMMENT\t*>          The name of the routine which called XERBLA.\nCOMMENT\t*> \\endverbatim\nCOMMENT\t*>\nCOMMENT\t*> \\param[in] INFO\nCOMMENT\t*> \\verbatim\nCOMMENT\t*>          INFO is INTEGER\nCOMMENT\t*>          The position of the invalid parameter in the parameter list\nCOMMENT\t*>          of the calling routine.\nCOMMENT\t*> \\endverbatim\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*  Authors:\nCOMMENT\t*  ========\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*> \\author Univ. of Tennessee\nCOMMENT\t*> \\author Univ. of California Berkeley\nCOMMENT\t*> \\author Univ. of Colorado Denver\nCOMMENT\t*> \\author NAG Ltd.\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*> \\date December 2016\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*> \\ingroup aux_blas\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*  =====================================================================\ntoken(96)\tSUBROUTINE\nIDENT\tXERBLA\n(\t(\nIDENT\tSRNAME\n,\t,\nIDENT\tINFO\n)\t)\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*  -- Reference BLAS level1 routine (version 3.7.0) --\nCOMMENT\t*  -- Reference BLAS is a software package provided by Univ. of Tennessee,    --\nCOMMENT\t*  -- Univ. of California Berkeley, Univ. of Colorado Denver and NAG Ltd..--\nCOMMENT\t*     December 2016\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*     .. Scalar Arguments ..\nIDENT\tCHARACTER\ntoken(95)\t*(\n)\t)\nIDENT\tSRNAME\nIDENT\tINTEGER\nIDENT\tINFO\nCOMMENT\t*     ..\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t* =====================================================================\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*     .. Intrinsic Functions ..\nIDENT\tINTRINSIC\nIDENT\tLEN_TRIM\nCOMMENT\t*     ..\nCOMMENT\t*     .. Executable Statements ..\nCOMMENT\t*\nIDENT\tWRITE\n(\t(\n*\t*,\nIDENT\tFMT\n=\t=\nIDENT\t9999\n)\t)\nIDENT\tSRNAME\n(\t(\nIDENT\t1\n:\t:\nIDENT\tLEN_TRIM\n(\t(\nIDENT\tSRNAME\n)\t)\n)\t)\n,\t,\nIDENT\tINFO\nCOMMENT\t*\nIDENT\tSTOP\nCOMMENT\t*\nIDENT\t9999\nIDENT\tFORMAT\n(\t(\nSTRING\t' ** On entry to '\n,\t,\nIDENT\tA\n,\t,\nSTRING\t' parameter number '\n,\t,\nIDENT\tI2\n,\t,\nSTRING\t' had '\n,\t,\nSTRING\t'an illegal value'\n)\t)\nCOMMENT\t*\nCOMMENT\t*     End of XERBLA\nCOMMENT\t*\nIDENT\tEND\n"
